will be futile, okay?
\N<Segi>...

\N<Subordinate Of Zeda>Don't think you can just waste time and say 'Okay, it's
done.' We'll need to see proof that you girls actually did
it, understand?
\N<Subordinate Of Zeda>Make sure that guy Rozaro inside knows too, heh...!
A

\N<Officer Luda>...Zeda.

\N<Zeda>Heh, you're earlier than I expected. I thought you'd be a
little later. But I'm not going to run or hide now.

\N<Zeda>Even so... the men of this town are pathetic. I thought
they'd hold out a little longer. They talk big about doing
it for their wives and unborn children, but in the end, this
is all they amount to.

\N<Zeda>Heh, it seems the mothers inside showed much more spirit,
didn't they?
\N<Officer Luda>Stop your prattling.
\N<Zeda>Yes, yes.
\N<Officer Luda>Come, you guys too.

\N<Resident>Wh-Why us too...!? Haven't you already eliminated those who
stood in your way?

\N<Officer Luda>Anyone who has once drawn a blade against us will easily do
so again with just a slight threat. We're nipping the bud of
rebellion now, that's what this is about.
